Normal Solomon has a great facility for turning a phrase: We can blame Bush all we want -- and he does hold the reins right now -- but his main enablers these days are the fastidious public servants in Congress. They keep preparing the hay, freshening the water, oiling the saddle, even while criticizing the inappropriately jocular rider. And when the band plays "Hail to the Jockey," most of the grown-up stable boys and girls can't help saluting.

The key problem right now isn't the headless jockey. It's the stable hands who keep feeding the horse he rode in on.
