This was also posted on The Huffington Post. I wrote that I agreed with a commenter who inquired "What are the Democrats waiting for?" They are, allegedly, supposed to be the voice of the people.

The commenter's question reminds me of the classic anti-war film The Train [1964], when, as the war is winding down, the French resistance is waiting for the Allies to show up before they march onto Paris to liberate that city. Burt Lancaster cries out "Where are the Allies?" Likewise, why are the Democrats not speaking out in a unified voice against the escalation, speaking out in favor of cutting off the funding, demanding that those troops be withdrawn from that quagmire as rapidly as possible? Where are the Democrats? It is almost as if the Republicans are still in power. It is way past the point that these pusillanimous Democrats should beseech the Wizard for a large heaping of courage.
